 <text>
  <front>
   <head>On the CRUCIFIXION.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">BEHOLD the Saviour of Mankind</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Nail'd to the shameful Tree!</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">How vast the Love that Him inclin'd</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">To bleed and die for Thee!</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Hark how he groans! while Nature shakes,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And Earth's strong Pillars bend!</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Temple's Veil in sunder breaks,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The solid Marbles rend.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Tis done! the precious Ransom's paid;</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Receive my Soul, he cries;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">See where he bows his sacred Head!</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">He bows his Head and dies.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But soon He'll break Death's envious Chain,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And in full Glory shine!</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">O Lamb of GOD, was ever Pain,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Was ever Love like Thine!</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
